@uppfinnarn and for buffers, you need to use dynamically sized ones wherever the length is externally determined, not buf[1024] /* enough?*/
@uppfinnarn you need to establish what is the "sane" range of every value you process and don't hesitate to reject.
@uppfinnarn int overflows often cause logical decisions to reverse
@uppfinnarn be very very very mindful of buffer and int overflows from parsed files.
@uppfinnarn if it's a web-facing application, external data is what keeps *voldemort* up at night.
@uppfinnarn other than that, it really depends on the language and whether it's a web program, desktop program, etc.
